<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="J" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Jill" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Jill</orth> (cf. <emph>Gill</emph>), a familiar name for a woman: <cit><quote>Jack hath not J.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.885" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 885</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Jack shall have J.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.461" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 461</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>be the jacks fair within, the --s fair without,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 52</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Jack.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>